Eight, CTO Shenzhen
Job Description】Job Responsibilities.
1, fully responsible for the technical team formation, echelon construction and all management of the company's technical level.
2, combined with the company's business development needs and the current state of the system, the development of technical development strategy, the system architecture development planning, organization and implementation of major technical decisions and programs.
3、Responsible for the planning, control, supervision and management of the technical solution design, development process, quality and development progress of the whole process from demand to delivery of the product, to ensure the development progress of the company's products, and to conduct quality assessment after completion.
4, the daily operation and maintenance of the platform system, risk audit, risk inspection and risk warning tips and solutions and other related work, and is responsible for system security and stability.
Job requirements.
1、Undergraduate degree or above, majoring in computer or software, with experience in architecture design, proficient in one or more mainstream blockchain system development languages such as go, java, C++, etc.
2、More than five years' experience in blockchain related technology development, more than three years' experience in R&D team management, managing a technical team of not less than 20 people.
3、Familiar with the underlying technology principle of blockchain, familiar with P2P network and distributed storage, familiar with the mainstream consensus mechanism.
4、Familiar with the implementation mechanism and operation principle of ipfs, filecoin, ethereum, openchain, bitcoin, hyperledger and other mainstream blockchain open source projects.
5、Familiar with various data structures and algorithms, research on distributed computing, security protocols, cryptographic algorithms and cloud computing.
6、In-depth understanding of the transaction system, and unique insights into the architecture and mechanism of the transaction system.
7、Strong learning, communication, expression and team management skills.
8、Those who have read the underlying source code and made relevant modifications, or those who have participated in the development of blockchain trading system and contributed source code are preferred.

