## Compound crisis exacerbates food security concerns

The 2022 Global Food Crisis Report released by the UN Food and Agriculture Organization (FAO) on May 4 local time shows that some 193 million people in 53 countries or regions worldwide experienced a food crisis or further deterioration in food insecurity in 2021, an increase of nearly 40 million people from 2020, a record high.

![Food crises happen every day](https://images.mirror-media.xyz/publication-images/L2JGHdKIQ24ozNEeQww3r.jpeg?height=782&width=1172)

Regions in Africa, Latin America and the Caribbean, and South and West Asia in Asia, experience widespread increases in undernourished populations between 2019 and 2020, reflecting the combined effect of the New Coronary Pneumonia epidemic and various factors that affect food security in the long term. In West Africa in particular, the malnourished population increases sharply by 5.8% to 24.6 million people in one year's time.

As we enter 2022, the goals of "poverty eradication" and "zero hunger" are further off track. The Russian-Ukrainian conflict, unilateralism and economic sanctions by the US and the West have significantly exacerbated the global economic downturn, and have had a strong impact on agricultural production, deepening the vulnerability of smallholder farmers and vulnerable groups in many regions, plunging some regions back into widespread poverty and turning some people into refugees. The tragic link between conflict and food insecurity has once again come to the fore and is cause for alarm," stressed FAO Director-General Qu Dongyu.

The FAO's Global Information and Early Warning System for Food and Agriculture (GIEWS) Special Early Warning Report on West Africa and the Sahara (No. 349), released on May 16, states that 27.3 million people in the region were severely food insecure from April to May, and if timely relief measures are not taken, the number will rise to 38.3 million by June to August. If timely relief measures are not taken, the number will increase to an unprecedented 38.3 million by June to August. UN Secretary-General Guterres said during his recent visit to Africa that the "triple crisis of food, energy and finance" is further intensifying.

Ukraine and Russia are the world's major food exporters, the current round of Russia-Ukraine conflict directly affected the summer harvest in Ukraine; the United States and Western countries on the Russian sanctions are unprecedented, resulting in a sharp rise in global food and fuel prices, once again pushed the world to the edge of the most serious crisis since the global food crisis in 2007 \~ 2008.

Many countries, especially developing countries in Africa, the Middle East and Latin America and the Caribbean, have already suffered from the combined effects of the epidemic of the century, regional conflicts and extreme weather caused by climate change in the past three years, especially the impact of record extreme weather such as ultra-high temperatures, mountain fires, droughts, storms and floods, and their current situation is even more difficult.

In Africa, for example, compared with 2021, food prices have risen by 1/3. So far this year, wheat and rice prices have soared by about 40% and 16%, respectively. According to the UN Food and Agriculture Organization report, the global food price index has reached record highs, in March has exceeded 159.7, breaking through the highest level in history. Even some European countries are not immune, the price index has recently increased by an average of about 20%.

Soaring agricultural prices and food prices have posed a huge threat to countries' food security. According to a report by the International Food Policy Research Institute (IFPRI), 23 countries have now turned to food protectionism. In fact, some countries such as India, Ukraine, Pakistan and Indonesia have explicitly issued relevant agricultural export restrictions.

## What we can do about the food crisis with blockchain

There are many reasons for the global food crisis. epidemic, industrial development, natural disasters, man-made destruction, reduction in the number of farmers, reduction in arable agricultural land, backward agricultural development in some regions, low agricultural production, and difficulty in selling agricultural products. We are not prepared to solve the above problems from the beginning. All problems, we want to solve one of them first, the reduction of agricultural land area and the problem of some agricultural land being abandoned.

We want to try to connect people in different regions with the help of blockchain, form a global organization, explore together to help agriculture, integrate more arable farmland here, link different roles of agricultural supply chain here, and finally To achieve the following objectives:

1. Let the abandoned farmland be used, make the best use of it, and give full play to its value;
2. Open up more farmland;
3. No longer prevent the cultivation of farmland because of difficult sales;
4. By linking different roles, open up the supply chain of agricultural products and export more agricultural products;
5. Strive to increase the output of agricultural products and solve the problem of food and clothing for more people;
6. Improve the quality of agricultural products and develop green and healthy agriculture;
7. Stop the global food crisis

we don't need to talk too much about blockchain and why choose blockchain not internet to stop global food crisis here.

